<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
/* Block element */
.block-example {
  display: block;
  background-color: lightblue;
  margin: 5px 0;
  padding: 10px;
}

/* Inline element */
.inline-example {
  display: inline;
  background-color: lightgreen;
  padding: 5px;
}

/* Inline-block element */
.inline-block-example {
  display: inline-block;
  background-color: lightcoral;
  padding: 10px;
  margin: 5px;
  width: 100px;
  height: 50px;
  text-align: center;
}

/* None element (hidden) */
.none-example {
  display: none;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Display Property Examples</h2>

<h3>Block</h3>
<div class="block-example">Block Element 1</div>
<div class="block-example">Block Element 2</div>
<p>Block elements start on a new line and take full width.</p>

<h3>Inline</h3>
<span class="inline-example">Inline 1</span>
<span class="inline-example">Inline 2</span>
<p>Inline elements stay on the same line and take only as much width as needed.</p>

<h3>Inline-block</h3>
<div class="inline-block-example">IB 1</div>
<div class="inline-block-example">IB 2</div>
<p>Inline-block elements stay on the same line but allow setting width/height.</p>

<h3>None</h3>
<div class="none-example">You won't see me because display is none</div>
<p>The above element is hidden and takes no space in the layout.</p>

</body>
</html>
